			<title>The Satanic Verses: The Original Incident Exposing Muhammad &amp; Revelation</title>
			<link>https://atheism-vs-islam.com/index.php/divine-revelation-or-human-drama/85-satanic-verses-the-original-incident-exposing-muhammad-revelation</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://atheism-vs-islam.com/index.php/divine-revelation-or-human-drama/85-satanic-verses-the-original-incident-exposing-muhammad-revelation</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<h2 class="_7T4UafM1PdBGycd5na9nF"><!--StartFragment --></h2>
<h2 class="_7T4UafM1PdBGycd5na9nF"><a class="mozTocH2" name="mozTocId255729"></a>Summary:</h2>
<p><!--StartFragment --></p>
<p>Differentiating between the real incident of the Satanic Verses and the fictitious novel by Salman Rushdie is of utmost importance. The authentic incident sheds light on the fallibility within the claimed divine revelation, challenging the existence of a heavenly Allah and suggesting that Muhammad himself was responsible for the revelation, resulting in human errors within it.</p>
<p>No other event exposes the human errors within the alleged divine revelation as clearly as the original incident of the Satanic Verses. Unfortunately, a vast majority of people, including Muslims, are unaware of this significant event.</p>
<p>The lack of awareness can be attributed to the confusion caused by Mr. Rushdie's fictional novel, also titled "Satanic Verses," which bears little resemblance to the actual incident. Regrettably, this misunderstanding has prevented the true incident of the Satanic Verses from reaching the masses. Presently, people struggle to distinguish between reality and fiction.</p>
